</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA3172CFFB81B52F6BCFCB19A1ED664" blockId="4.[151,1436,739,946]" box="[199,1365,775,802]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis id="B968CB3EFFB81B52F6BCFCB19E2AD667" bold="true" box="[199,353,775,801]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">Distribution.</emphasis>
All the zoogeographical regions, except 
<collectingCountry id="F30B57BCFFB81B52F551FCB19CD4D667" box="[810,927,775,801]" name="Antarctica" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">Antarctica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D6ADDFFB81B52F5D5FCB19B60D667" author="Olmi, M." box="[942,1067,775,801]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309" pagination="85 - 146" refId="ref11351" refString="Olmi, M. (1996) A revision of the world Embolemidae (Hymenoptera Chrysidoidea). Frustula Entomologica, 17, 85 - 146." type="journal article" year="1996">Olmi 1996</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D6ADDFFB81B52F24DFCBE9B3AD664" author="Olmi, M." box="[1078,1137,776,802]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309" pagination="125 - 150" refId="ref11378" refString="Olmi, M. (1997) A contribution to the knowledge of the Embolemidae and Dryinidae (Hymenoptera Chrysidoidea). Bollettino di Zoologia Agraria e Bachicoltura, 29, 125 - 150." type="journal article" year="1997">1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D6ADDFFB81B52F206FCB19A02D664" author="Cheny, C. &amp; Guillam, E. &amp; Nel, A. &amp; Perrichot, V." box="[1149,1353,775,802]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref10231" refString="Cheny, C., Guillam, E., Nel, A. &amp; Perrichot, V. (2020) A new species of Ampulicomorpha Ashmead from Eocene French amber, with a list of fossil and extant Embolemidae (Insecta: Hymenoptera) of the world. BSGFeEarth Sciences Bulletin, 191 (20), 1 - 7. https: // doi. org / 10.1051 / bsgf / 2020020" type="journal article" year="2020">
Chény 
<emphasis id="B968CB3EFFB81B52F2B6FCBE9A4ED667" box="[1229,1285,775,801]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA3172CFFB81B52F6BCFC9A9D8CD600" blockId="4.[151,1436,739,946]" box="[199,711,811,838]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis id="B968CB3EFFB81B52F6BCFC9A9E3FD603" bold="true" box="[199,372,811,838]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">World species.</emphasis>
24 species (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D6ADDFFB81B52F786FC9D9DF7D600" author="Olmi, M. &amp; Marletta, A. &amp; Guglielmino, A." box="[509,700,811,838]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309" pagination="40 - 48" refId="ref11647" refString="Olmi, M., Marletta, A. &amp; Guglielmino, A. (2020) The first record of the family Embolemidae (Hymenoptera: Chrysidoidea) in Reunion, with description of a new species of Embolemus Westwood. Israel Journal of Entomology, 50 (1), 40 - 48." type="journal article" year="2020">
Olmi 
<emphasis id="B968CB3EFFB81B52F43BFC9A9D33D603" box="[576,632,811,837]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA3172CFFB81B52F6BCFCE69DD4D6C8" blockId="4.[151,1436,739,946]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis id="B968CB3EFFB81B52F6BCFCE69E4DD62C" bold="true" box="[199,262,848,874]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">Host.</emphasis>
Ectoparasitoids of nymphs of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C6CAFFFB81B52F425FCF99D80D62F" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1866" box="[606,715,847,873]" class="Insecta" family="Achilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Achilidae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C1C6CAFFFB81B52F4A1FCF99C1DD62F" box="[730,854,847,873]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Hemiptera</taxonomicName>
: Auchenorrhyncha, Fulgoromorpha) living in rotten logs and feeding on fungus (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D6ADDFFB81B52F7AEFCC59DD8D6C8" author="Olmi, M. &amp; Belokobylskij, S. A. &amp; Guglielmino, A." box="[469,659,883,910]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309" pagination="97 - 108" refId="ref11462" refString="Olmi, M., Belokobylskij, S. A. &amp; Guglielmino, A. (2014) Revision of the family Embolemidae of Russia and Ukraine (Hymenoptera: Chrysidoidea), with description of a new species. Annales Zoologici, 64 (1), 97 - 108. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 000345414 X 680672" type="journal article" year="2014">
Olmi 
<emphasis id="B968CB3EFFB81B52F46CFCC29D1BD6CB" box="[535,592,883,909]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA3172CFFB81B52F6BCFC2E9A14D6F4" blockId="4.[151,1436,739,946]" box="[199,1375,919,946]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis id="B968CB3EFFB81B52F6BCFC2E9E4DD6F4" bold="true" box="[199,262,920,946]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">Note.</emphasis>
Here, the genus is recorded for the first time from the Middle East, 
<collectingCountry id="F30B57BCFFB81B52F27BFC2E9B66D6F4" box="[1024,1069,920,946]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">Iran</collectingCountry>
(marked with an Asterisk).
</paragraph>
